{"word":"κτῆσις","slug":"κτῆσις","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κτῆσις</b></el> <el>(κτῆσις, εως) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:κτάομαι'><el>κτάομαι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>acquisition</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>; <el>κατ' ἔργου κτῆσιν</el> according to <i>success in</i> the work, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>(from <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a>) <i>possession</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>as collective, = <el>κτήματα</el>, <i>possessions, property</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>; in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}